<section class="section" id="testing">
    <h2 class="mc-heading reveal">Testing the Prototype</h2>
    <p class="reveal">Testing the prototype (created from the second version of hifi wireframes) in Figma went surprisingly well, and I did not have much to change or improve, so I started coding.</p>

    <h2 class="mc-heading reveal">Testing the coded website</h2>
    <p class="reveal">When I tested the website again, I finally found what I did wrong. I gave it to four people for testing and overall feedback, and all of them had problems with the toggle on the phone - in my head, they would just click on the camera (or text), but they all tried to swipe. This bug is still not fixed because I can't figure out how, but I am working on it.</p><br>

    <p>One feedback said that it is hard to tell from the landing page that the website is about photography. This should not be an issue (in my opinion) because people will come from advertisements on Facebook or from the Instagram profile, already knowing who Michaela Cibulková is. I might be wrong, and if so, we will make changes to address this issue.</p>
